Q.1 Who is credited with the REST approach to web services?
A.1 Roy Fielding

Q.2 What Python library do you have to import to parse and handle JSON?
A.2 import json

Q.3 What is the method used to parse a string containing JSON data so that you can work with the data in Python?
A.3 json.loads()

Q.4 What kind of variable will you get in Python when the following JSON is parsed:
    { "id" : "001",
       "x" : "2",
       "name" : "Chuck"
    }
    
A.4 A dictionary with three key / value pairs

Q.5 Which of the following is not true about the service-oriented approach?
A.5 An application runs together all in one place

Q.6 Which of these two web service approaches is preferred in most modern service-oriented applications?
A.6 REST - Representational state transfer

Q.7 What library call do you make to append properly encoded parameters to the end of a URL like the following:
    http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?sensor=false&address=Ann+Arbor%2C+MI
    
A.7 urllib.parse.urlencode()

Q.8 What happens when you exceed the Google geocoding API rate limit?
A.8 You cannot use the API for 24 hours

Q.9 What protocol does Twitter use to protect its API?
A.9 OAuth

Q.10 What header does Twitter use to tell you how many more API requests you can make before you will be rate limited?
A.10 x-rate-limit-remaining

Q.11 Which of the following is true about an API?
A.11 An API is a contract that defines how to use a software library



